# Fake News Detection with Explainable AI

This project detects whether a news article is REAL or FAKE using a lightweight BERT model and generates an explanation using a local language model.
The application allows users to input either text or a URL, classify the content, retrieve verified context from Wikipedia, and generate a human-readable explanation.

## Features

- Fake news classification using BERT-tiny
- Explainable AI using a local language model
- Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
- Web scraping for article extraction
- Streamlit web interface

## Tech Stack

Python  
Streamlit  
Transformers (Hugging Face)  
BeautifulSoup  
Wikipedia API  
Torch

## How it Works

1. User enters article text or URL
2. Article is classified as REAL or FAKE using a BERT model
3. Relevant context is retrieved from Wikipedia
4. A local language model generates an explanation
5. A moderation report can be downloaded

## Installation

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/aswinsajji/fake-news-detection

Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Run the application:
streamlit run app.py

## Example Use Case

This tool can assist:
- social media moderators
- journalists
- fact-checking organizations
by quickly identifying suspicious content and providing explainable results.

## Future Improvements

- Improve RAG retrieval using vector databases
